<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8613&amp;p=89906#p89906"><![CDATA[
I believe that using the emulator's export function is always better than using a generic screen capture program over the emulator window... The reason being that an emulator is guaranteed to write all video frames to the output file, while the screen capture program is likely to drop frames (capturing at 60fps isn't easy).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Mon Feb 13, 2012 6:36 am</p><hr />
